parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and stalling can cause a loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle's speed is limited to 20 mph or less
the "Reduced Engine Power" message appears on the dashboard
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle may not respond to acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brakes can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: requiring multiple pumps or pressing the pedal all the way to the floor to engage
and the vehicle may roll or move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS actuator can cause the anti-lock braking system to malfunction, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS actuator failure warning message appears on the instrument panel
and the vehicle may experience reduced braking performance or unusual braking behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to severe injuries or fatalities, as seen in the reported cases of concussion and neck and back trauma.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
despite the severity of the impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden brake lock-up can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes lock up without warning
causing the vehicle to skid or crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccessible recall repair can leave vehicles with known safety defects on the road, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are unable to access recall repair services due to location or logistical constraints.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, hesitation, and stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine temperature gauge displays higher temperatures

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injector can cause the engine to run rough, reduce fuel mileage, and trigger the engine warning light, which can lead to engine stalling, loss of power, and decreased vehicle safety.
Engine performance issues can cause the engine to run rough, reduce fuel mileage, and trigger the engine warning light, which can lead to engine stalling, loss of power, and decreased vehicle safety.
